    {
      "id": "PopularPost321378",
      "post_content": "\"*Why oh why couldn't it be a common now? I want to Unearth it in Pauper :)*\"  \n  \n@Earthdawn They want to keep their Commons simple.  \nEpocharasite is probably considered too complex as a Common card:  \nIt gets counters, but only if it's not cast normally. It gets suspended when it dies, which means it needs to be taken care of with yet another kind of counters in exile each turn...  \n  \nIf every Common required that much attention, Drafts would get a lot less straight-forward.  \nThen again, there are a couple of similar exceptions, and it doesn't hurt if only about 1% of the Commons are like this.  \n  \nAdmittedly, i'd have like the idea at least as much as you do, even if only for the fact that jumps from Rare to Common and vice versa are hilarious. (Thinking of [another, very particular 1/1 for two mana](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=14720) - that actually managed to pull off in both directions.)",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost321378\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_post\">\"<i>Why oh why couldn't it be a common now? I want to Unearth it in Pauper :)</i>\"<br/><br/>@Earthdawn They want to keep their Commons simple.<br/>Epocharasite is probably considered too complex as a Common card:<br/>It gets counters, but only if it's not cast normally. It gets suspended when it dies, which means it needs to be taken care of with yet another kind of counters in exile each turn...<br/><br/>If every Common required that much attention, Drafts would get a lot less straight-forward.<br/>Then again, there are a couple of similar exceptions, and it doesn't hurt if only about 1% of the Commons are like this.<br/><br/>Admittedly, i'd have like the idea at least as much as you do, even if only for the fact that jumps from Rare to Common and vice versa are hilarious. (Thinking of <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardid=\"14720\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=14720\">another, very particular 1/1 for two mana</a> - that actually managed to pull off in both directions.)</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl05_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '321378'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy416\">Mode</span>\r\n                                (6/1